HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 687
By Love
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Dr. William E. Arnold, Jr.,
for his contributions to the State of Tennessee.
WHEREAS, it is our privilege to specially recognize those estimable individuals who,
through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community leaders of
whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Dr. William E. Arnold, Jr., a highly respected
individual who has dedicated himself to justice and community empowerment; and
WHEREAS, in 2013, Dr. William Arnold was wrongfully convicted in Nashville; his
conviction was unanimously overturned by the Tennessee Court of Criminal Appeals in 2020,
making him the first individual to receive relief from the Davidson County Conviction Review
Unit; and
WHEREAS, April 15, 2025, marks the fifth anniversary of Dr. Arnold's exoneration, a
powerful milestone that symbolizes the triumph of truth, the promise of second chances, and the
enduring strength of the human spirit; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Arnold has since transformed his experience into purpose, using his
platform to promote labor-focused reentry strategies that restore dignity, reduce recidivism, and
build equitable workforce opportunities for justice-involved individuals; and
WHEREAS, a native of Memphis, Dr. Arnold is the founder and diversity compliance
officer of Arnold Diversity Consulting in Memphis, which engages organizations in an effort to
effect culture change, organizational development, and process improvement; and
WHEREAS, he also currently serves as director of the Tennessee Office of Reentry
within the Department of Labor and Workforce Development, the first comprehensive, state-
funded, non-Department-of-Correction-affiliated reentry office in the nation; and
